graphviz-reload: Used as an informational message to inform the user to reload the wiki page.
graphviz-dot-invalid-image:
Used as error message.  Parameters:
* $1 - attribute name
graphviz-dot-attr-forbidden:
Used as an error message.  Parameters:
* $1 - attribute name
graphviz-delete-reason: Describes the reason for deleting an uploaded file.
graphviz-alt: This is the default alt text for a graph image if the user does not supply alt text. This is intended for visually impaired readers.
graphviz-upload-comment:
Comment supplied for an image uploaded by the extension.  Parameters:
* $1 - article title
graphviz-unrecognized-preparse-value:
Used as error message.  Parameters:
* $1 - attribute name
graphviz-category-desc:
GraphViz category page text.  Parameters:
* $1 - GraphViz category tag
graphviz-subcategory-desc:
GraphViz subcategory page text.  Parameters:
* $1 - GraphViz subcategory tag
* $2 - graph render command associated with subcategory
graphviz-map-desc: Do not translate the tags , , or . Parameters: * $1 - image file name * $2 - image map shape, coordinates and URL (0 or more lines)
graphviz-upload-user: The username of the user that graph images should be uploaded as (if the current user doesn't have permission)
